        "# Symmetry breaking, symmetry perfection, and gauge in LLM parameter space\n",
        "\n",
        "Six perturbation arms on the cyclic token structure (months) in the **input embedding\n",
        "matrix**. Not activations — this is a parameter-space experiment by design.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "## THE SETUP (read this — it corrects two natural misconceptions)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Misconception 1: \"circle = symmetry, deviation = noise around it.\"** False. Every\n",
        "Fourier mode is an irrep of Z/12. A circle-only configuration is *exactly as\n",
        "symmetric* as the full structure. Deleting modes is irrep deletion at **constant\n",
        "symmetry**, not symmetry destruction. (This is why an ablation of the k>=2 modes\n",
        "cannot support a symmetry claim.)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Misconception 2: \"equivariance is the obvious thing to measure.\"** Also treacherous.\n",
        "The Z/12 symmetry means an orthogonal R exists with X_{t+1} = R X_t, which requires\n",
        "the row-Gram to be **circulant**. But random rows in high d are near-orthonormal, so\n",
        "their Gram ~ I, which *is* circulant — random embeddings are **trivially\n",
        "near-equivariant**. Measured here: delta_equi(random) = 0.383 (d=16), 0.099 (d=64),\n",
        "0.025 (d=256), 0.005 (d=1024). At LLM widths a *low* defect means nothing.\n",
        "\n",
        "Therefore: the **primary symmetry measure is per-mode circularity s2/s1** (dimension\n",
        "independent; real LLMs measure 0.86–0.96), and delta_equi is reported only against a\n",
        "random null at the same d.\n",
        "\n",
        "**What actually has content:** *linear* cyclic covariance is vacuous — the Fourier\n",
        "basis is complete, so **every** configuration of 12 points admits a linear map\n",
        "implementing the shift. The only non-vacuous notion is **isometric** equivariance\n",
        "(the shift is an *orthogonal* map), and that is exactly what circularity controls.\n",
        "\n",
        "**So the question this experiment asks is:**\n",
        "> Does the modular-arithmetic mechanism depend on the **metric** structure of the\n",
        "> cyclic representation (isometric equivariance), or only on its **linear** structure?\n",
        "\n",
        "A validated mock (two readers with known mechanisms — an orthogonal-shift reader and\n",
        "an unconstrained-linear-shift reader) confirms the design can **discriminate** these:\n",
        "under symmetry-breaking the metric reader degrades (1.000 -> 0.939) while the linear\n",
        "reader does not (1.000). **The honest prior is ~50/50.** A null result means \"the\n",
        "mechanism is not metric-sensitive,\" which is publishable but quieter.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "## PRE-REGISTERED PLAN — frozen before running.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Arms** (all applied to the 12 month rows of the input embedding; invariants asserted\n",
        "at runtime by `assert_invariants`):\n",
        "\n",
        "| arm | perturbation | preserves | breaks | role |\n",
        "|---|---|---|---|---|\n",
        "| **A** | `cyclic_relabel(s)` — exact group element | everything incl. delta_equi | nothing | **positive control**: answers must shift by exactly *s* |\n",
        "| **B1** | `gauge_perturb` — commutant (per-mode phase), **input only** | circularity, energies, delta_equi | absolute positions | symmetry-preserving damage baseline |\n",
        "| **B2** | same gauge element applied to input **and unembedding** rows | as B1 | as B1 | **gauge-invariance test**: does behaviour *recover* when the reader is co-transformed? |\n",
        "| **C** | `break_symmetry(lam)` — ellipticity at fixed per-mode energy | energies, distinguishability | **isometric equivariance** | **THE CORE TEST** (dose over lam) |\n",
        "| **D** | `perfect_symmetry` — equalise mode svals | energies | the imperfection (delta_equi -> 0) | **is the imperfection load-bearing?** |\n",
        "| **E** | `matched_random` | energy only | everything | baseline |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Magnitude matching.** Arms are compared at equal relative Frobenius perturbation\n",
        "(`match_magnitude`), and BOTH matching criteria (frob, mean per-token displacement)\n",
        "are reported — a reviewer will attack the normalisation, so the conclusion must be\n",
        "shown robust to which one is used. Note D is *intrinsically small* in real LLMs\n",
        "(circularity already 0.86–0.96), so D-vs-C is matched at the natural size of D.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Tasks.** Modular: months (a + k) mod 12, >=5 templates, all (a,k). Identity\n",
        "controls over the SAME tokens: season, ordinal (within-year, NOT \"month after\" — that\n",
        "is +1 mod 12), monthnum where single-token. Readouts: accuracy AND **logit margin**\n",
        "(season sits at ~0.93; accuracy will ceiling and mask damage).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Primary statistic.** DiD = (modular damage) − (identity damage) under the same\n",
        "perturbation, with the item-cluster bootstrap CI (`did_bootstrap`).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Hypotheses (pre-committed).**\n",
        "- H-A: arm A shifts the modal answer by exactly *s* (targeted-shift rate >= 3x chance).\n",
        "  **If A fails, the whole experiment is void** — the structure is not being read at all\n",
        "  and nothing downstream is interpretable.\n",
        "- H-C (core): DiD_C > 0, CI excludes zero, and monotone in lam (Page's L, one-sided).\n",
        "- H-C-vs-B (the real test): **DiD_C > DiD_B1 at matched magnitude.** B1 preserves every\n",
        "  symmetry invariant yet still perturbs; C additionally breaks the symmetry. Only the\n",
        "  *difference* isolates the symmetry.\n",
        "- H-B2 (gauge invariance): behaviour under B2 recovers toward intact relative to B1.\n",
        "  Genuinely uncertain — the network's nonlinearity may break gauge invariance.\n",
        "- H-D: if perfecting symmetry *reduces* accuracy, the imperfection is load-bearing\n",
        "  (surprising, and the most interesting single outcome available here).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Decision rules.**\n",
        "- H-C holds AND DiD_C > DiD_B1 → the mechanism reads the *metric* structure. Claim.\n",
        "- DiD_C ~ DiD_B1 → damage is generic; the symmetry is not what is read. **Report as a\n",
        "  null**; do not rescue by re-matching magnitudes until it works.\n",
        "- A fails → void; report and stop.\n",
        "- Any post-hoc deviation from these rules must be labelled as such in the writeup.\n"
