      "source": [
        "## Reading the outcome (pre-committed — do not renegotiate)\n",
        "\n",
        "- **A fails** → the structure is not being read at all; everything else is void. Stop.\n",
        "- **DiD_C > 0 (CI excludes 0) AND DiD_C > DiD_B1** → the mechanism reads the *metric*\n",
        "  structure of the cyclic representation. This is the claim. Report the dose curve.\n",
        "- **DiD_C ≈ DiD_B1** → damage is generic; the symmetry per se is not what the\n",
        "  computation reads. **This is a null and must be reported as one.** Do not re-tune the\n",
        "  magnitude matching until it passes.\n",
        "- **D reduces accuracy** → the *imperfection* is load-bearing: forcing perfect symmetry\n",
        "  hurts. Most surprising available outcome; report prominently either way.\n",
        "- **B2 recovers relative to B1** → behavioural gauge invariance in a real LLM: the\n",
        "  network's function is unchanged when the structure and its reader are co-transformed\n",
        "  by the same commutant element. If it does *not* recover, the nonlinearity breaks\n",
        "  gauge invariance — also a real finding.\n",
        "\n",
        "Two standing caveats to carry into the writeup: (i) delta_equi is only meaningful\n",
        "against its random null at the same width; (ii) *linear* cyclic covariance is vacuous,\n",
        "so all claims here are about **isometric** equivariance and nothing more."
